description._content: Funeral Procession of Mrs. Sundstedt, circa June 14, 1924 General Notes: Written on verso: "Services lasting over an hour with [services] appropriate to occasion by fellow workers and friends. Beginning with a song in English “The Red Flag.” After which recitation and speeches by [?] fellow workers followed. The services ended with last verse of same song. As we marched away the revolutionary funeral song was sung by a group of Russian workers. Mrs. Sundsedt, as well as her little family, were loved by her fellow workers of San Pedro." Photographer: E. F. Moffett Subjects (LCSH): Industrial Workers of the World -- History. Industrial Workers of the World.
